disillusion /ˌdɪsɪˈluːʒən/

(disillusioning,disillusioned,disillusions) 

1. V-T If a person or thing disillusions you, they make you realize that something is not as good as you thought. 使醒悟 

例： I'd hate to be the one to disillusion him. 我不愿做打破他梦想的人。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Disillusion is the same as . 幻灭 

例： There is disillusion with established political parties. 对各个确立的政党有幻灭感。

